"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The `plt.text` function requires the x and y coordinates to be within the limits of the axes. If the x-coordinate (a date) is outside the range of the x-axis limits set by the data in `df['C']`, it will not display correctly. The code does not check if the date is within the range of the x-axis.\",\n  \"patch\": \"17c17\\n< plt.text(datetime.datetime.strptime(\\\"2013-01-05\\\"), 0.5, \\\"SAMPLE\\\")\\n---\\n> if df['C'].min() <= datetime.datetime.strptime(\\\"2013-01-05\\\") <= df['C'].max():\\n>     plt.text(datetime.datetime.strptime(\\\"2013-01-05\\\"), 0.5, \\\"SAMPLE\\\")\"\n}"